<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-172-410  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 172 410.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC World  March 1990 v8 n3 p66(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Epson America stirs: printer giant challenges leaders. (IndustryOutlook) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hogan, Mike.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Epson America introduced its first laser printer at a price $800below the Hewlett-Packard Laser-Jet II, then slashed an additional$600 off the price and offered a $195 PostScript-clone option for$40 in response to HP's release of the Laser-Jet IIP, in anaggressive move not typical of the firm's recent history.andP;  Butcompany executives say the days of merely maintaining the statusquo are over.andP;  The firm plans increasingly competitive technology,typified by the removable screen and drives of its LT-286e laptop.andO;Both customers and resellers give Epson high marks forsatisfaction and the firm was recently named service vendor of theyear by ComputerLand.andP;  Most of Epson's revenues have been inlower-end products, and the firm must build a solid customer basein the more profitable 386 and 486 markets to be profitable.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Epson America Inc. (marketing).andO;Topic:     Hardware VendorsMarketing StrategyMicrocomputersCompetition.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>